## 6. Cross-Platform Considerations

### 6.1 macOS vs Windows Scroll Direction

| Platform | Default Scroll Direction |
|----------|--------------------------|
| macOS (trackpad) | "Natural" (content follows fingers) |
| macOS (mouse) | Same as trackpad (unless changed) |
| Windows | "Traditional" (opposite of macOS) |
| Linux | Varies by desktop environment |

**Recommendation:** Use the raw `deltaY` value directly. Browser vendors have already normalized for user preferences. Do NOT attempt to detect or reverse scroll direction.

### 6.2 Platform-Specific deltaY Magnitude

| Platform | Typical deltaY (mouse) | Typical deltaY (trackpad) |
|----------|------------------------|---------------------------|
| Windows Chrome | 100 | 1-10 (many events) |
| macOS Chrome | 100 | 0.5-3 (many events) |
| Windows Firefox | 3 (LINE mode) | 1-2 |
| macOS Safari | 12-30 | 0.5-2 |

### 6.3 Recommended Normalization Strategy

```typescript
const ZOOM_SENSITIVITY = 0.001;  // Base sensitivity
const MAX_ZOOM_DELTA = 0.5;      // Cap per event

function calculateZoomDelta(event: WheelEvent): number {
  let delta = event.deltaY;

  // Normalize LINE mode to pixels
  if (event.deltaMode === 1) {
    delta *= 16; // Approximate line height
  }

  // Apply sensitivity and clamp
  delta *= ZOOM_SENSITIVITY;
  delta = Math.max(-MAX_ZOOM_DELTA, Math.min(MAX_ZOOM_DELTA, delta));

  return delta;
}
```

